  "title": "Genotyping Finger Millet Germplasm –Developing a Composite Collection",
  "abstract": "Finger millet [Eleusine coracana\r\n(L.) Gaertn.] belongs to family\r\nPoaceae. It is a tetraploid\r\nspecies with 2n=36, and selfpollinating.\r\n• Cultivated in 23 countries on\r\n3.38 million ha producing 3.76\r\nm t mainly in Africa and Asia.\r\n• A very important crop in\r\nUganda, Nepal, Kenya, Ethiopia, Eritrea and India.\r\n• Nutritionally rich in protein, minerals and metionine amino acid...",
